  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: all versions\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\nCommit hash : all versions\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nNote spec at https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC:\n\n> When encoding QUANTITIES (integers, numbers): encode as hex, prefix with \"0x\", the most compact representation (slight exception: zero should be represented as \"0x0\").\n\nMake JSONRPC call and give a JSON integer as an argument; expected result is \"Invalid Arguments\" error.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\ngeth interprets the JSON integer as the according `QUANTITY` argument.\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nGiven above.\n",
